  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3459460/extras/828dda2e75e62b5a7e8c4d96f6bd0832.poster.avif?t=1739305948\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3459460/extras/828dda2e75e62b5a7e8c4d96f6bd0832.webm?t=1739305948\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3459460/extras/828dda2e75e62b5a7e8c4d96f6bd0832.mp4?t=1739305948\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The game is a simulator of the Macro Data Refinement terminal - a mysterious console where you have to find the right numbers and collect them in groups of 9. The right numbers complete the percentage of file refinement, and completing the game and getting the prize requires completing 100% refinement of individual data files. Can you do it?</p>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3459460/extras/828dda2e75e62b5a7e8c4d96f6bd0832.poster.avif?t=1739305948\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3459460/extras/828dda2e75e62b5a7e8c4d96f6bd0832.webm?t=1739305948\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3459460/extras/828dda2e75e62b5a7e8c4d96f6bd0832.mp4?t=1739305948\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The game is a simulator of the Macro Data Refinement terminal - a mysterious console where you have to find the right numbers and collect them in groups of 9. The right numbers complete the percentage of file refinement, and completing the game and getting the prize requires completing 100% refinement of individual data files. Can you do it?</p>",
